Description:

Complete the solution so that it returns true if the first argument(string) passed in ends with the 2nd argument (also a string).

Examples:

Inputs: "abc", "bc"
Output: true

Inputs: "abc", "d"
Output: false

--- 

My solution :

#include <stdbool.h>

bool solution(const char *string, const char *ending)
{ 
  
  int string_length = 0;
  int ending_length = 0;
  
  while (string[string_length] != '\0') string_length++;
  while (ending[ending_length] != '\0') ending_length++;
  
  if(ending_length > string_length) return false;

  while(ending_length > 0) {
    if(ending[ending_length-1] != string[string_length-1]) {
      return false;
    } 
      string_length--;
      ending_length--; 
  }
  return true;
}

